docs.abstract: The terrorist attack in New Zealand is shocking on every level — and feels like a first for how unmistakably online it was.
docs.snippet: The terrorist attack in New Zealand is shocking on every level — and feels like a first for how unmistakably online it was.
docs.lead_paragraph: Before entering a mosque in Christchurch, New Zealand, the site of one of the deadliest mass murders in the country’s history, a gunman paused to endorse a YouTube star in a video that appeared to capture the shooting.

headline.main: A Mass Murder of, and for, the Internet
headline.print_headline: A Shooting Disturbingly Rooted in the Internet
